<caption><i>2nd-level transmutation</i>
</caption>
<tbody><tr>
<th>Casting Time
</th><td>1 action
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>Range
</th><td>60 feet
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>Components
</th><td>V S M (Iron, fire)
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>Duration
</th><td>Conc. Up to 1 minute
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>A <a href="/wiki/Creature" title="Creature">creature</a> in contact with a metal object you can see takes 2d8 <a href="/wiki/Damage_Type#Fire" title="Damage Type">fire</a> damage. If it's holding or wearing the object, they must pass a <a href="/wiki/Constitution" title="Constitution" class="mw-redirect">Constitution</a> save or drop it. If it doesn't drop the object, it has <a href="/wiki/Disadvantage" title="Disadvantage" class="mw-redirect">disadvantage</a> on attack rolls and ability checks. On subsequent turns while it's in contact with the object, you can inflict the damage again as a bonus action.
</p><p><b>At Higher Levels:</b> The damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 2nd.
</p>
